Uh... look around.

1223
01:11:06,469 --> 01:11:09,300
Do you, um-- do you
notice anything different?

1224
01:11:10,834 --> 01:11:13,901
Uh-- um-- hm.

1225
01:11:13,936 --> 01:11:15,734
Hmm...

1226
01:11:15,769 --> 01:11:17,667
Oh! Is this it?
No.

1227
01:11:17,702 --> 01:11:18,868
Thank God.

1228
01:11:18,903 --> 01:11:20,534
[laughs]
Okay...

1229
01:11:20,569 --> 01:11:22,334
Keep looking!
Keep looking!
Okay okay okay!

1230
01:11:22,369 --> 01:11:24,901
New rug!
No! Wow! Not even close!

1231
01:11:24,936 --> 01:11:27,467
Wow! You're really
not good at this game!
Mm-hm.

1232
01:11:31,434 --> 01:11:32,701
Wow, that never gets old.

1233
01:11:32,736 --> 01:11:35,534
Come on! Just tell me!
What what what? I give up!

1234
01:11:35,569 --> 01:11:38,467
All right. You're all
out of guesses. Poor effort.
But all right.

1235
01:11:38,502 --> 01:11:41,734
Your life's work?
The manuscripts? Look around.

1236
01:11:41,769 --> 01:11:42,901
They're gone.

1237
01:11:46,000 --> 01:11:47,067
Is this... a joke?

1238
01:11:47,102 --> 01:11:50,334
No, no, no, no!
No joke, Miss Malone.

1239
01:11:50,369 --> 01:11:52,701
You are being published.

1240
01:11:56,501 --> 01:11:58,934
Well... I don't
know what to say.

1241
01:11:58,969 --> 01:12:04,901
Well, traditionally--
"Thank you, Brandon!"
would suffice.

1242
01:12:04,936 --> 01:12:06,067
Thank you.

1243
01:12:09,000 --> 01:12:11,667
How dare you?

1244
01:12:11,702 --> 01:12:13,300
[scoffing snort] What?

1245
01:12:16,534 --> 01:12:19,000
I mean-- how pathetic
do you think I am,

1246
01:12:19,035 --> 01:12:20,834
that-that-that you'd
have to--

1247
01:12:20,869 --> 01:12:22,133
buy that for me, too?
[groans]

1248
01:12:22,168 --> 01:12:24,334
Do you think maybe
I might wanna earn that?

1249
01:12:24,369 --> 01:12:26,167
You can't buy me
success!

1250
01:12:26,202 --> 01:12:27,834
No! Megan, no! No!

1251
01:12:27,869 --> 01:12:30,834
He and I thought that--
Oh, he! He! It's a he!

1252
01:12:30,869 --> 01:12:34,834
Who is he? Just-- come on!
Maggie-- I can't
tell you that!

1253
01:12:34,869 --> 01:12:35,968
Those were the rules!
You know that!

1254
01:12:36,003 --> 01:12:37,667
You know what?
Enough of the rules!

1255
01:12:37,702 --> 01:12:39,934
Okay? Maybe you should try
breaking the rules,

1256
01:12:39,969 --> 01:12:41,234
for once in your life.

1257
01:12:44,200 --> 01:12:46,000
[sighs]

1258
01:12:46,035 --> 01:12:48,534
Maggie-- I can't.

1259
01:12:52,367 --> 01:12:54,334
You can't, or you won't?

1260
01:12:58,033 --> 01:12:59,167
It-- [sighs]

1261
01:13:01,701 --> 01:13:03,634
Forget it.
Hey, wait. No.
Hang on a second!

1262
01:13:03,669 --> 01:13:06,567
[stammers] Wait, Maggie.
What about the kiss?

1263
01:13:06,602 --> 01:13:09,868
The kiss was a mistake, okay?
This whole thing has been
a mistake!

1264
01:13:09,903 --> 01:13:13,200
This is not my life--
Wait, Maggie--!
D-Don't...

1265
01:13:16,734 --> 01:13:18,601
[exhales hard]

1266
01:13:29,300 --> 01:13:30,901
[elevator rings, opens]

1267
01:14:59,901 --> 01:15:02,634
## <i>[opera]</i>

1268
01:15:06,801 --> 01:15:08,868
[Brandon]
So she insists on knowing.

1269
01:15:08,903 --> 01:15:10,567
I mean, just your name
would do, I'm sure.

1270
01:15:10,602 --> 01:15:12,234
What is that?

1271
01:15:12,269 --> 01:15:14,667
Is that a stain
in your tie?

1272
01:15:14,702 --> 01:15:17,100
Oh. Ketchup, sir.

1273
01:15:17,135 --> 01:15:20,467
Formed quite an addiction
to these hot dogs.

1274
01:15:20,502 --> 01:15:22,033
Will there be
anything else, sir?

1275
01:15:22,068 --> 01:15:23,734
No, Samuel. Thank you.

1276
01:15:23,769 --> 01:15:25,100
Very good, sir.
That will be all.

1277
01:15:26,634 --> 01:15:28,300
[Brandon]
I don't understand.
I mean--

1278
01:15:28,335 --> 01:15:31,567
it can't go on this way
forever. I myself am curious--

1279
01:15:31,602 --> 01:15:34,567
I don't pay you
to be curious.

1280
01:15:34,602 --> 01:15:36,234
It's not pertinent
to my interests.

1281
01:15:38,901 --> 01:15:41,000
And your interest,
by the way, is not
to compromise mine.

1282
01:15:41,035 --> 01:15:43,334
All right? It's to serve it!

1283
01:15:43,369 --> 01:15:45,534
I got 20 years of research
into this. Have you?

1284
01:15:47,033 --> 01:15:49,133
What do you think? I can
afford to lose her again?

1285
01:15:49,168 --> 01:15:52,734
'Cause you can't execute
a stupid lousy instruction!

1286
01:15:52,769 --> 01:15:55,300
News?
Hey, Samuel? Sit down!

1287
01:15:55,335 --> 01:15:57,767
I'm sorry. Could you go
to my closet

1288
01:15:57,802 --> 01:16:00,400
and get him a selection
of ties to try on? He's
got this stain, here.

1289
01:16:00,435 --> 01:16:02,767
Very good, sir.

1290
01:16:25,734 --> 01:16:28,200
## <i>[pop --</i>
<i>"Daydream Believer"]</i>

1291
01:16:32,167 --> 01:16:34,634
# <i>Oh, I could hide</i> #

1292
01:16:34,669 --> 01:16:36,834
# <i>'Neath the wings</i> #

1293
01:16:36,869 --> 01:16:38,868
# <i>Of the bluebird</i> #

1294
01:16:38,903 --> 01:16:41,467
# <i>As she sings</i> #

1295
01:16:41,502 --> 01:16:42,667
[Man] Hey, Maggie.
I'll be right with ya.

1296
01:16:42,702 --> 01:16:44,834
# <i>The 6:00 alarm</i> #

1297
01:16:44,869 --> 01:16:46,734
# <i>Would never ring</i> #

1298
01:16:49,000 --> 01:16:51,000
# <i>But it rings</i> #

1299
01:16:51,035 --> 01:16:53,234
# <i>And I rise</i> #

1300
01:16:53,269 --> 01:16:54,534
# <i>Wipe the sleep</i> #

1301
01:16:54,569 --> 01:16:57,067
# <i>Out of my eyes</i> #

1302
01:16:57,102 --> 01:16:59,467
Hey, George.

1303
01:16:59,502 --> 01:17:00,701
I got something for ya.

1304
01:17:04,167 --> 01:17:06,200
What's this?

1305
01:17:06,235 --> 01:17:07,667
For years of--

1306
01:17:07,702 --> 01:17:09,200
exceptional--

1307
01:17:09,235 --> 01:17:11,200
bike-watching service.

1308
01:17:11,235 --> 01:17:12,300
See ya.
Wha--?

1309
01:17:13,467 --> 01:17:17,467
# <i>To a daydream believer</i> #

1310
01:17:17,502 --> 01:17:20,701
# <i>And a homecoming...</i> #
Ohh... [hits ground]

1311
01:17:20,736 --> 01:17:22,133
# <i>Queen</i> #

1312
01:17:22,168 --> 01:17:24,534
[Forelli]
Hey, Maggie!
You little <i>canole</i>!

1313
01:17:24,569 --> 01:17:25,634
How's it goin'?

1314
01:17:25,669 --> 01:17:27,634
Hey.

1315
01:17:27,669 --> 01:17:28,934
Oh, almost forgot.

1316
01:17:28,969 --> 01:17:30,901
Here's for all that
rent I owe you.

1317
01:17:30,936 --> 01:17:32,734
And that new roof
you've been wanting.

1318
01:17:32,769 --> 01:17:35,968
# <i>Now you know</i>
<i>How happy</i> #

1319
01:17:36,003 --> 01:17:38,133
# <i>I can be</i> #

1320
01:17:39,834 --> 01:17:42,767
# <i>And our good times...</i> #

1321
01:17:42,802 --> 01:17:45,100
[Maggie]
Did you ever think
I was scared?

1322
01:17:45,135 --> 01:17:47,400
I don't know--
fear of failure?

1323
01:17:47,435 --> 01:17:49,801
Fear of success. Whatever
those shrinks call it.

1324
01:17:53,033 --> 01:17:55,901
I don't know. I guess--

1325
01:17:55,936 --> 01:17:58,968
I just never thought
I was good enough
to be published.

1326
01:17:59,003 --> 01:18:01,834
The point is, you're
a published writer.

1327
01:18:03,567 --> 01:18:05,133
Yeah.

1328
01:18:05,168 --> 01:18:07,601
Only catch is,
I didn't earn it.

1329
01:18:11,334 --> 01:18:12,667
[rattling]
What the--?

1330
01:18:12,702 --> 01:18:15,000
[Brandon, outside]
Maggie!
[rocks on window]

1331
01:18:15,035 --> 01:18:16,467
Maggie!

1332
01:18:16,502 --> 01:18:18,868
Oh my God, it's him!
[squeaks]

1333
01:18:18,903 --> 01:18:20,834
[Brandon]
Maggie!

1334
01:18:20,869 --> 01:18:22,567
Please!

1335
01:18:22,602 --> 01:18:25,100
Come on!

1336
01:18:25,135 --> 01:18:27,334
Maggie, I must
talk to you!

1337
01:18:27,369 --> 01:18:30,534
How romantic.
Oh, he scores points.
Very <i>Romeo and Juliet</i>.

1338
01:18:30,569 --> 01:18:32,534
And that accent's sexy!
[giggling]

1339
01:18:32,569 --> 01:18:34,767
Get away! I don't want him
to know I'm in here!

1340
01:18:34,802 --> 01:18:37,801
[Brandon]
I know you're in there!
I saw your bicycle!

1341
01:18:37,836 --> 01:18:38,734
Damn it.

1342
01:18:42,701 --> 01:18:44,834
Go away!
Maggie, please!

1343
01:18:44,869 --> 01:18:47,934
[stammering]
I-I-I must talk to you!

1344
01:18:47,969 --> 01:18:49,501
I don't talk to liars!

1345
01:18:49,536 --> 01:18:52,868
I didn't lie! I-- omitted!

1346
01:18:52,903 --> 01:18:54,567
Same difference!

1347
01:18:54,602 --> 01:18:57,100
Don't be an idiot!
The man is fighting for you!

1348
01:18:57,135 --> 01:19:00,734
This knight-in-shining-
armor crap doesn't come by
too often.

1349
01:19:00,769 --> 01:19:02,634
## <i>[rock -- "I Want</i>
<i>You to Want Me"]</i>
<i>[on stereo, outside]</i>

1350
01:19:05,100 --> 01:19:07,067
Wait! Stop. Stay.
Don't move.

1351
01:19:09,267 --> 01:19:13,567
# <i>I want you to want me</i> #

1352
01:19:13,602 --> 01:19:17,767
# <i>I need you to need me</i> #
What are you doing?

1353
01:19:17,802 --> 01:19:19,367
[shouting]
I want you to know

1354
01:19:19,402 --> 01:19:23,534
that you've turned me
into a couch potato!

1355
01:19:23,569 --> 01:19:27,367
I rented every circa
1980's American film

1356
01:19:27,402 --> 01:19:30,033
to try to figure out
how to win you back!

1357
01:19:30,068 --> 01:19:33,234
I ran across this
terribly sappy gesture,

1358
01:19:33,269 --> 01:19:34,901
but I thought you'd
like it!

1359
01:19:34,936 --> 01:19:38,467
# <i>I'd love you</i>
<i>to love me</i> #
And if you don't,

1360
01:19:38,502 --> 01:19:41,067
I'll climb up the trellis!

1361
01:19:42,834 --> 01:19:44,868
Though I'd really
rather not. Looks
quite perilous.

1362
01:19:48,033 --> 01:19:49,567
Don't bother.

1363
01:19:49,602 --> 01:19:51,400
You might break
a nail or something.

1364
01:19:53,067 --> 01:19:55,200
Just take the stairs.

1365
01:19:55,235 --> 01:19:58,300
# <i>Diddle-I diddle-l</i>
<i>Diddle-I see you cryin'</i> #

1366
01:19:58,335 --> 01:19:59,667
Stairs?

1367
01:19:59,702 --> 01:20:01,334
Trellis would have
been easier.

1368
01:20:01,369 --> 01:20:02,400
[shuts off music]

1369
01:20:04,501 --> 01:20:05,834
[Bridgette]
This is so cool!

1370
01:20:05,869 --> 01:20:06,868
Oh, no no no no.

1371
01:20:06,903 --> 01:20:08,968
You're not watching
a blow-by-blow,

1372
01:20:09,003 --> 01:20:10,801
play-by-play whatever.
Go go go! Out out!

1373
01:20:10,836 --> 01:20:12,801
You are a terrible friend.
We are old married biddies,

1374
01:20:12,836 --> 01:20:14,734
and need to live
vicariously through you.

1375
01:20:14,769 --> 01:20:16,167
Yeah. Sorry to disappoint.

1376
01:20:16,202 --> 01:20:18,634
I'm a terrible friend.
Now go. Go! Out. Out.

1377
01:20:18,669 --> 01:20:20,801
[door opens]

1378
01:20:20,836 --> 01:20:22,300
Hello.
Hi!

1379
01:20:23,601 --> 01:20:24,634
Good luck.

1380
01:20:27,367 --> 01:20:29,767
[panting]

1381
01:20:32,400 --> 01:20:33,367
Um...

1382
01:20:40,234 --> 01:20:41,868
Ta-dah!

1383
01:20:46,400 --> 01:20:47,868
Very cute.

1384
01:20:47,903 --> 01:20:50,033
Now say whatever it is
you gotta say.

1385
01:20:50,068 --> 01:20:51,734
Okay. Warm welcome.

1386
01:20:51,769 --> 01:20:54,300
Well, I'll-- I'll just
get straight to it, then.

1387
01:20:54,335 --> 01:20:55,634
Umm...

1388
01:20:55,669 --> 01:20:58,434
See... the thing is...

1389
01:20:58,469 --> 01:21:00,968
all my life, I have
sort of thought of myself

1390
01:21:01,003 --> 01:21:02,934
as a bit...

1391
01:21:02,969 --> 01:21:05,167
passionless, for lack
of a better word.

1392
01:21:06,734 --> 01:21:09,434
Until... recently.

1393
01:21:09,469 --> 01:21:11,400
See... [sighs]

1394
01:21:11,435 --> 01:21:13,901
The truth is, Maggie...

1395
01:21:13,936 --> 01:21:16,501
I've... fallen for you.

1396
01:21:16,536 --> 01:21:19,767
I... I think about you
incessantly,

1397
01:21:19,802 --> 01:21:22,801
and, um, I think that I...

1398
01:21:22,836 --> 01:21:25,567
[sighs]...love you.

1399
01:21:25,602 --> 01:21:27,400
Now, I-I-I-I realize that

1400
01:21:27,435 --> 01:21:29,033
I have a lot to live up to,

1401
01:21:29,068 --> 01:21:31,267
what with you writing
about princes and whatnot.

1402
01:21:31,302 --> 01:21:34,000
And though I may not have
rode here on my white horse

1403
01:21:34,035 --> 01:21:37,300
-- I can't ride -- um,

1404
01:21:37,335 --> 01:21:41,400
I will do everything
in my power

1405
01:21:41,435 --> 01:21:43,834
to make you feel
like a princess,

1406
01:21:43,869 --> 01:21:45,367
every day,

1407
01:21:45,402 --> 01:21:47,200
for the rest of my life.

1408
01:21:55,501 --> 01:21:56,934
Any response to that?

1409
01:21:58,100 --> 01:22:00,200
Really, anything at all
will do.

1410
01:22:02,400 --> 01:22:03,834
Uh--

1411
01:22:03,869 --> 01:22:05,501
no.

1412
01:22:05,536 --> 01:22:07,400
I mean...

1413
01:22:07,435 --> 01:22:08,968
it doesn't really matter
what I feel,

1414
01:22:09,003 --> 01:22:10,934
or what I don't
feel for you.

1415
01:22:10,969 --> 01:22:12,200
The reality is,

1416
01:22:12,235 --> 01:22:13,467
I can't trust you.

1417
01:22:17,434 --> 01:22:20,000
You're right. I won't tell you
who the benefactor is.

1418
01:22:20,035 --> 01:22:22,267
See? I mean, I don't even
know why you came here--
I'll show you.

1419
01:22:22,302 --> 01:22:23,734
It doesn't even--
what?

1420
01:22:26,634 --> 01:22:27,767
I said I will show you

1421
01:22:27,802 --> 01:22:29,267
who your benefactor is.

1422
01:22:31,033 --> 01:22:32,167
You will lose
all of the money,

1423
01:22:32,202 --> 01:22:35,200
and I will be fined,
if not disbarred,

1424
01:22:35,235 --> 01:22:38,734
for breach of attorney/client
confidentiality. But, um...

1425
01:22:40,601 --> 01:22:42,567
for you, Miss Malone?

1426
01:22:42,602 --> 01:22:44,934
I'm prepared to break
the rules.

1427
01:22:44,969 --> 01:22:48,200
On one condition.

1428
01:22:48,235 --> 01:22:50,067
You let me finish
that kiss you started.

1429
01:22:52,534 --> 01:22:53,467
Hmm.

1430
01:22:55,434 --> 01:22:57,067
That's very sketchy
behavior.
Mm-hmm.

1431
01:22:58,234 --> 01:23:01,133
Trading kisses
for information.

1432
01:23:01,168 --> 01:23:03,601
Mmm.
Extortion. Blackmail,
some might say.

1433
01:23:03,636 --> 01:23:04,934
But...

1434
01:23:04,969 --> 01:23:07,267
But, alas, I seem
to have no choice.

1435
01:23:15,367 --> 01:23:17,033
[cooing, smooching]

1436
01:23:19,868 --> 01:23:21,801
[big sigh]

1437
01:23:21,836 --> 01:23:23,267
I've been, um...

1438
01:23:23,302 --> 01:23:25,300
thinking about you
incessantly, also.

1439
01:23:25,335 --> 01:23:26,367
Really.
Yeah.

1440
01:23:26,402 --> 01:23:27,801
Well, that works out well.
Mm-hm.

1441
01:23:27,836 --> 01:23:31,100
[chuckling]
[kissing, moaning]

1442
01:23:33,167 --> 01:23:35,334
Oh. I already spent
all the money.

1443
01:23:35,369 --> 01:23:37,467
Mm... good lord!
On what?

1444
01:23:37,502 --> 01:23:38,667
Umm... college.

1445
01:23:40,634 --> 01:23:43,033
A new roof.
And a security guard.

1446
01:23:43,068 --> 01:23:44,901
My God. Big spender!

1447
01:23:47,033 --> 01:23:49,701
I can't think of
anyone I'd rather
live in poverty with.

1448
01:23:49,736 --> 01:23:52,434
You say the sweetest things.

1449
01:23:52,469 --> 01:23:54,200
All right, enough about...

1450
01:23:54,235 --> 01:23:55,334
I am a man of my word,

1451
01:23:55,369 --> 01:23:56,901
and I still have to
pay out for that first kiss.

1452
01:23:56,936 --> 01:23:58,767
So, uh... let's bugger off.

1453
01:24:00,200 --> 01:24:01,467
Oh. My sweater.

1454
01:24:04,100 --> 01:24:05,367
Wait! I don't have
any shoes!

1455
01:24:05,402 --> 01:24:06,801
Don't... forget your shoes.

1456
01:24:17,667 --> 01:24:19,033
I'll go check the study.

1457
01:25:00,667 --> 01:25:02,634
Can't find him.

1458
01:25:02,669 --> 01:25:03,601
Who's that?

1459
01:25:06,667 --> 01:25:07,667
That's me.

1460
01:25:10,934 --> 01:25:12,400
[footsteps]

1461
01:25:27,033 --> 01:25:28,133
Daddy?

1462
01:26:01,200 --> 01:26:03,701
[church bells]

1463
01:26:22,267 --> 01:26:24,534
[soft chatter]

1464
01:26:28,167 --> 01:26:30,267
You must be proud.
Uh-huh!

1465
01:26:30,302 --> 01:26:32,734
[soft muttering]

1466
01:26:34,200 --> 01:26:36,200
Hey, hey. Shh.
Calm down.

1467
01:26:36,235 --> 01:26:40,901
I'm nervous.
[laughs]

1468
01:26:40,936 --> 01:26:42,968
## <i>[church organ, loud]</i>

1469
01:26:47,501 --> 01:26:50,634
## <i>[wedding march]</i>

1470
01:27:37,367 --> 01:27:38,767
Thanks.

1471
01:27:42,367 --> 01:27:43,534
Hi.
Hi!

1472
01:27:57,300 --> 01:27:58,367
[Man in back]
Wait!

1473
01:28:00,901 --> 01:28:01,834
Maggie?

1474
01:28:20,534 --> 01:28:23,601
Don't make me run.

1475
01:28:23,636 --> 01:28:25,334
I've got a bum knee.

1476
01:28:27,834 --> 01:28:28,968
You don't recall?

1477
01:28:31,334 --> 01:28:33,367
[panting]

1478
01:28:35,033 --> 01:28:36,534
Do you have any
recollections of us?

1479
01:28:38,601 --> 01:28:40,367
You don't recall
when Mommy died.

1480
01:28:41,534 --> 01:28:42,667
[bitter laugh]

1481
01:28:44,801 --> 01:28:47,767
You and I hit
the road, kid.

1482
01:28:47,802 --> 01:28:49,167
Like a pair of hobos.

1483
01:28:50,767 --> 01:28:51,934
Mom was a...

1484
01:28:53,968 --> 01:28:55,367
'Course, we ended up
in the street.

1485
01:28:58,601 --> 01:29:01,133
How was I gonna button
my own shirt, let alone
tell you a story?

1486
01:29:03,734 --> 01:29:05,601
I gave you to a church.

1487
01:29:05,636 --> 01:29:08,234
Just to get my head
straight, you know?

1488
01:29:08,269 --> 01:29:10,734
I come back after
a few months.
They deny me access.

1489
01:29:12,300 --> 01:29:14,067
Then I go back to
the church, to petition
the records.

1490
01:29:14,102 --> 01:29:16,267
The records are sealed.

1491
01:29:16,302 --> 01:29:19,367
I had to get permission.
You talk about humiliation.

1492
01:29:19,402 --> 01:29:22,767
Had to get permission
just to write.

1493
01:29:22,802 --> 01:29:23,834
So I wrote.

1494
01:29:26,968 --> 01:29:29,434
I wrote you a letter a month,
for 10 years, Mags.

1495
01:29:31,601 --> 01:29:32,767
You never answered.

1496
01:29:37,334 --> 01:29:38,901
I figured you just
threw 'em away.

1497
01:29:41,567 --> 01:29:43,234
A few weeks ago, I'm
in London. I get a call

1498
01:29:43,269 --> 01:29:45,467
from some woman named Lettie.
She says she found
the letters.

1499
01:29:48,167 --> 01:29:49,501
Why?

1500
01:29:54,100 --> 01:29:57,033
The letters just
came too late.

1501
01:30:05,601 --> 01:30:08,000
You know how many years
I looked for you?

1502
01:30:11,100 --> 01:30:13,200
I named my first kitten
"Daddy",

1503
01:30:13,235 --> 01:30:15,000
just so I could
say it out loud.

1504
01:30:20,267 --> 01:30:22,901
But I'll call you
Bernard, for now.

1505
01:30:22,936 --> 01:30:24,133
If that's okay.

1506
01:30:26,234 --> 01:30:28,901
That is your name,
isn't it?
Yeah.

1507
01:30:28,936 --> 01:30:29,901
[sniffles]

1508
01:30:31,300 --> 01:30:33,767
I gotta know
one thing, Bernard.

1509
01:30:33,802 --> 01:30:35,701
[sniffles]

1510
01:30:35,736 --> 01:30:38,234
Why the whole ruse?

1511
01:30:38,269 --> 01:30:40,267
You know, and
<i>Great Expectations</i>
and everything.

1512
01:30:40,302 --> 01:30:42,033
That was very creative.

1513
01:30:45,067 --> 01:30:46,934
Why not just call me up
and say,

1514
01:30:48,701 --> 01:30:50,968
"Hi. I'm your dad.

1515
01:30:51,003 --> 01:30:52,033
"Let's go to lunch."

1516
01:30:58,067 --> 01:30:59,701
I guess we get scared.

1517
01:30:59,736 --> 01:31:02,167
Right.

1518
01:31:03,534 --> 01:31:05,334
It's a common defect.

1519
01:31:09,100 --> 01:31:12,968
I would love nothing more
than to take you to lunch.

1520
01:31:16,200 --> 01:31:20,400
Well, you know,
I've kinda got a wedding

1521
01:31:20,435 --> 01:31:22,334
to finish in there.

1522
01:31:27,167 --> 01:31:28,234
Well...

1523
01:31:30,033 --> 01:31:31,133
Shall we?

1524
01:31:33,334 --> 01:31:35,234
We shall.

1525
01:31:46,701 --> 01:31:49,133
Otherwise, why
would he come?

1526
01:32:02,801 --> 01:32:05,100
Okay, let's go.
Come on, come on.

1527
01:32:36,868 --> 01:32:39,334
You take care of
my little girl.

1528
01:32:39,369 --> 01:32:41,767
I will, sir.

